The paper focuses on software testing and analysis, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for clear definitions and identification of relevant sub-domains, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) or systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions vulnerabilities and failures in code, which could fall under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes the use of information-theoretic distance functions, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
